rë:^<?php exit; ?>a:1:{s:7:"content";a:49:{s:8:"produits";a:1:{i:0;s:1:"3";}s:18:"penci_recipe_title";a:1:{i:0;s:33:"Chicory Salad and stuffed cabbage";}s:21:"penci_recipe_servings";a:1:{i:0;s:0:"";}s:21:"penci_recipe_preptime";a:1:{i:0;s:10:"30 minutes";}s:28:"penci_recipe_preptime_format";a:1:{i:0;s:0:"";}s:21:"penci_recipe_cooktime";a:1:{i:0;s:10:"30 minutes";}s:28:"penci_recipe_cooktime_format";a:1:{i:0;s:0:"";}s:25:"penci_recipe_instructions";a:1:{i:0;s:1587:"&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;For the chicory salad:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Cover the bottom of the bento with some shoots of lamb‚Äôs lettuce.&lt;br /&gt;Remove the first leaves from the chicory. Place these leaves in your bento box.&lt;br /&gt;Cut the goat cheese into small cubes.&lt;br /&gt;Cut the pear in halfs lengthwise, hollow out the pear and cut into thin slices.&lt;br /&gt;Add the goat's cheese pieces, thin slices of pear and pecans to the heart of the chicory leaves.&lt;br /&gt;Sprinkle your salad with a few pumpkin seeds.&lt;br /&gt;Fill your MB Temple sauce container with balsamic vinegar and olive oil as a salad dressing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;For the stuffed cabbage:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Boil a pot of water.&lt;br /&gt;Blanch the cabbage leaf for 10 minutes.&lt;br /&gt;Dice the mushrooms and potato, then mince the onions.&lt;br /&gt;In a saucepan, fry the mushrooms, potato pieces and onion in olive oil for 10 minutes, then add the mustard.&lt;br /&gt;Spread the green cabbage leaf in an ovenproof dish. Garnish it with the stuffing and close the cabbage leaf by folding it over itself.&lt;br /&gt;Bake at 180¬∞C for 20 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To complete this meal, add orange pieces and shortbreads.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Zero waste tips:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;- Keep the orange peels to make ‚Äúorangettes‚Äù or a delicious marmalade&lt;br /&gt;- Buy your vegetables in bulk by bringing your own containers&lt;br /&gt;- Use organic fruit and veggies to keep their skin on&lt;br /&gt;- Use leftover pie dough to make shortbreads!&lt;/p&gt;";}s:24:"penci_recipe_ingredients";a:1:{i:0;s:406:"<p>For 1 MB Original bento box:</p>
<p>Salad:<br />- A little chicory<br />- 20g of goat cheese<br />- Some shoots of lamb‚Äôs lettuce<br />- A handful of pecan nuts<br />- Some squash seeds<br />- A pear</p>
